      <hr>
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <p>Note that documents the use of the 1XX subject or authorized subdivision heading as an
         example or reference in fields 260 Complex See Reference, 360 Complex See Also
         Reference, and/or 680 Public General Note in another authority record.
      </p>
      <p>Permits the updating of the 260, 360, or 680 field when a change is made to the 1XX
                     heading.
      </p>
      <p>Information in this field is often not written in a form adequate for public user
                     display.      </p>
      <hr>
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> INDICATORS
      </h4>
      <ul>
         <li>Both indicator positions are undefined; each contains a blank (#).</li>
      </ul>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> SUBFIELD CODES
      </h4>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$a - Subject heading or subdivision term</strong> <div class="description">1XX heading of the record that contains the 260, 360, and/or 680 fields in which
                              an established subject or authorized subdivision heading is cited.
         </div>
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
